, density, nesting, and visual weight distribution.",variants:3},{id:"vibes",label:"Explore different vibes",labelId:"canvas.makeVariants.presetVibes",prompt:"Generate 3 variations of the selected component that explore different aesthetic and tonal directions while preserving the current layout and structure. Each variation should evoke a distinct emotional register — consider dimensions like warmth, density, formality, playfulness, and visual quietness. These are not random color swaps; each should feel like a coherent design opinion.",variants:3},{id:"polish",label:"More like this, but better",labelId:"canvas.makeVariants.presetPolish",prompt:"Generate 2 variations of the selected component that refine and polish the current direction. Identify what's already working well and produce tighter versions that resolve rough edges, improve consistency, and strengthen the existing design intent without changing the fundamental approach.",variants:2},{id:"usability",label:"Optimize for usability",labelId:"canvas.makeVariants.presetUsability",prompt:"Generate 3 variations of the selected component that each prioritize a different usability dimension: clarity of information hierarchy, ease of interaction and affordance visibility, and accessibility and readability. Each variation should make a specific usability tradeoff explicit rather than trying to optimize everything at once.",variants:3},{id:"opposite",label:"Show me the opposite of this",labelId:"canvas.makeVariants.presetOpposite",prompt:"Generate 2 variations of the selected component that invert its dominant design choices. Identify the strongest assumptions in the current design — its density, tone, structure, interaction pattern, or visual approach — and explore what happens when you go the other direction. The goal is to surface hidden constraints and assumptions by contrast.",variants:2},{id:"surprise",label:"Surprise me",labelId:"canvas.makeVariants.presetSurprise",prompt:"Analyze the selected component and i